		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName> <date>July 31st 5625</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(10)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
				<p><add>Hebrew</add></p>
				<p><persName role="author">Michael Light</persName></p>
				<p><placeName>94 East Broadway</placeName></p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>N. Y.</placeName> <date>July 31&#44; 5625 &#40;1865</date>&#41;.</p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>&#44; <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>&#44;</p>
				<p>Honored Sir&#58;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">I have received your honored letter and&#44; therefore&#44; send you<lb/> the <persName>Moses</persName> and <persName>Aaron</persName>&#42; that you desired.  <persName>Holzman</persName> <sic>departedmfor</sic> the <placeName>West</placeName> 2<lb/> months ago.  The wholesale price of the pictures is &#36;.50 each.  The<lb/> enclosed bill is being sent to you in order to show it to the customer<lb/> because I sell such at a retail price of &#36;1.  <persName>Mr. Moss</persName> will not come<lb/> until <date>Rosh Hashonah</date>&#44; and I shall write to him about the penitential<lb/> hymn&#45;book for <date>Tish&#45;a&#45;b&#39;av</date>.  <persName>Mr. Bondi</persName> has until this moment not de&#45;<lb/>livered anything masterful.  The next issue will appear in a new shape<lb/> and is to bear the title&#44; &#8220;Shomer Israel&#8221;.  It is feared that he will lose<lb/> money&#44; since the first issue contained over 130 typographical errors&#44; i. e.<lb/> in the German article.  Moreover&#44; a new weekly is appearing here.  If<lb/> you have a <hi rend="underline">free</hi> opportunity to have someone take something along&#44; send<lb/> me 6 prayer books&#44; &#8220;Dibrei Zaddikim&#8221;&#44; in ordinary binding&#44; because I hope<lb/> to do some more business for you before <date>Rosh Hashonah</date>.  I shouldn&#39;t like<lb/> to pay for freight.</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)">Respectfully&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(9)">Your most devoted friend&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(10)"><persName role="author">Michael Light</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(11)"><placeName>94 East Broadway</placeName></p>
				<p>&#42; <persName>Moses</persName> and <persName>Aaron</persName> is the name of the two rollers upon which the Torah is<lb/> rolled.</p>
		</body>
